Dahl
Judy Heumann

1 cup dried lentils
2 cups water
2 tbsp oil
1 large onion
garlic
1/2 tsp turmeric
1/2 tsp cumin
a pinch of cayenne pepper
1/4 tsp salt
1 tsp garam masala
  or:
    1/8 tsp cloves
    1/4 tsp cinnamon
    1/4 tsp cardamom
    1/4 tsp corriander
  or:
    1 tsp curry


Cook lentils in cups water, covered, until tender (about 30 minutes).  Heat oil in large pot and sautee onion and garlic.  Add spices and continue cooking one more minute.  Add lentils and cook about 10-15 minutes, until spices are well blended.

You can add any of the following steamed veggies: broccoli, cauliflower, carrots.  Uncooked cabbage, thinly sliced can also be added.

Serve with millet, plain yogurt, cut up tomatoes and cucumbers.
